COPS in Maake, outside Tzaneen, in Limpopo have opened a case of inquest after a four-year-old boy was electrocuted to death by an open live wire at Burgersdorp Village on Sunday, 12 June. According to Lieutenant-Colonel Mamphaswa Seabi, it is alleged that the boy was walking with his siblings from their aunt’s place when the tragic incident happened at about 5.30pm. “The children ran home to inform their mother that their younger brother was shocked by an open live wire that was lying on the ground. “The victim was certified dead on the scene by the medical emergency personnel,” Seabi said in a statement. He said a case of inquest has been registered for further investigation. Meanwhile, the provincial commissioner of police in Limpopo, Lieutenant-General Thembi Hadebe has urged residents to report illegal electricity connections to the police to prevent these type of incidents from happening.